    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>FORMER G.M. EXECUTIVE SOUGHT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Edmund L. Andrews</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Andrews, Edmund L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>US Justice Dept petitions Spain to extradite former General Motors employee Jose Ignacio Lopez de Arriortua, accused of stealing vast quantities of GM documents (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The United States Justice Department formally petitioned Spain to extradite Jose Ignacio Lopez de Arriortua to stand trial in the United States on charges of industrial espionage. Mr. Lopez left the Opel subsidiary of General Motors in Germany to go to Volkswagen in 1992, and General Motors accused him of stealing vast quantities of documents -- many later shredded -- when he left. Volkswagen pushed out Mr. Lopez in late 1996 and in 1997 settled lawsuits with General Motors.</p>
        <p>Edmund L. Andrews (NYT)</p>
      </block>
